2026-04-21 01:31:05 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control module input cables between power supply module and control module'] hypothesis_explanation='The measured −12 V on the conductor believed to be the ‘+’ line means the two conductors between the power‑supply module output and the control module input are connected with reversed polarity. With the control-module LED wired to light when its two input lines are reversed, this explains why the red LED on the control cube is on. Because the control module then delivers reversed polarity to the load module, the diode in series with the bulbs in the load module blocks current, so neither the main lamp nor the internal indicator lamp can turn on. Correcting the polarity of the two cables between power supply and control module (swapping them at either end) should restore normal operation, with the green LED on, the red LED off, and the lamp operating when the switch is closed.'
